tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE social_media_engagement (
    influencer_id INT,
    fashion_show_id INT,
    engagement_score FLOAT,
    collaboration_type VARCHAR(50),
    audience_comments TEXT,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE SocialMediaEngagement (
    post_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    post_content TEXT,
    likes INT,
    comments INT,
    shares INT,
    influencer_id UUID,
    created_at TIMESTAMP
)

CREATE TABLE SocialMediaEngagement (
   engagement_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
   show_id INT,
   influencer_id INT,
   engagement_date DATE,
   likes_count INT,
   comments_count INT,
   shares_count INT,
   FOREIGN KEY (show_id) REFERENCES FashionShows (show_id),
   FOREIGN KEY (influencer_id) REFERENCES Influencers (influencer_id)
);

CREATE TABLE AudienceMetrics (
   metrics_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
   engagement_id INT,
   unique_views_count INT,
   total_views_count INT,
   click_through_rate FLOAT,
   engagement_rate FLOAT,
   FOREIGN KEY (engagement_id) REFERENCES SocialMediaEngagement (engagement_id)
);

CREATE TABLE FashionShows (
    show_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    show_name VARCHAR(100),
    start_date DATE,
    end_date DATE,
    location VARCHAR(100)
);

CREATE TABLE EngagementMetrics (
    metrics_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    collab_id INT,
    likes_count INT,
    comments_count INT,
    shares_count INT
);
